The paper discusses the problem of personalization in interactive systems such as search engines and recommender systems, which falls under the category of human-computer interaction (cs.HC). The proposed solution involves learning users' reward functions using inverse reinforcement learning techniques, which is a subfield of artificial intelligence (cs.AI) and machine learning (cs.LG). The paper also mentions the use of user features in the learning process, which is related to information retrieval (cs.IR) and cybersecurity (cs.CY).
